entry.summary: We prove that a compact, immersed, submanifold of C^n, lagrangian for a Kahler form, is rationally convex, generalizing a theorem of Duval and Sibony for embedded submanifolds.

entry.summary: A formula for the variance of the spectrum of a quasihomogeneous singularity is proved, using the G-function of a semisimple Frobenius manifold.

entry.summary: We give a characterization of $L_h^2$-domains of holomorphy with the help of the boundary behavior of the Bergman kernel and geometric properties of the boundary, respectively.

entry.summary: The reflection function of a smooth CR diffeomorphism between two minimal real analytic hypersurfaces is everywhere real analytic.

entry.summary: We provide a classification of complex projective surfaces with a holomorphic foliation whose group of birational symetries is infinite.

entry.title: Oka's principle for holomorphic fiber bundles with sprays
entry.summary: We give a proof of the following theorem of M. Gromov (Oka's principle for holomorphic sections of elliptic bundles, J. Amer. Math. Soc., 2 (1989), 851-897). Let Z be a holomorphic fiber bundle over a Stein manifold. If the fiber of Z admits a dominating holomorphic spray then the inclusion of the space of global holomorphic sections of Z into the space of continuous sections is a weak homotopy equivalence. In the classical case when the fiber is a complex Lie group or a homogeneous space this was proved by H. Grauert (Math. Ann., 135 (1958), 263--273). For further results in this direction see the papers math.CV/0101040, math.CV/0101040, math.CV/0101034, math.CV/0101238, math.CV/0107039, math.CV/0110201.

entry.summary: The floating body approach to affine surface area is adapted to a holomorphic context providing an alternate approach to Fefferman's invariant hypersurface measure.

entry.summary: We prove the existence and study the geometry of Bishop discs near an elliptic point of a real n-dimensional submanifold of an almost complex n-dimensional manifold.

entry.title: The symmetrized polydisc cannot be exhausted by domains biholomorphic to convex domains
entry.summary: We prove that the symmetrized polydisc cannot be exhausted by domains biholomorphic to convex domains.

entry.title: The relative extremal function for Borel sets in complex manifolds
entry.summary: We study a disc formula for the relative extremal function for Borel sets in complex manifolds.

entry.summary: This article uses basic homological methods for evaluating examples of compactly supported cohomology groups of line bundles over projective curve.

entry.title: Gluing complex discs to Lagrangian manifolds by Gromov's method
entry.summary: The paper discusses some aspects of Gromov's theory.

entry.title: Squares of positive $(p,p)$-forms
entry.summary: We show that if $\alpha$ is a positive $(2,2)$-form then so is $\alpha^2$. We also prove that this is no longer true for forms of higher degree.

entry.title: Comparison of invariant funcions and metrics
entry.summary: In this short note it is shown that all invariant metrics and functions of bounded $\mathcal C^2$-smooth domain coincide on an open non-empty subset.
entry.arxiv:comment: A draft version. Any comments are welcome

entry.title: Subelliptic estimates for the dbar-problem on a singular complex space
entry.summary: We prove subelliptic estimates for the dbar-problem at the isolated singularity of the variety $z^2=xy$ in $\mathbb{C}^3$.

entry.title: The critical points of a polynomial
entry.summary: In this paper, we obtain new results on the critical points of a polynomial, these results are useful to the Sendov conjecture.

entry.title: On quaternionic functions
entry.summary: Several sets of quaternionic functions are described and studied. Residue current of the right inverse of a quaternionic function is introduced in particular cases.

entry.title: On an analogue of Schwarz's reflection principle
entry.summary: We consider the Bergman space on the complex plane. We prove an analogue of Schwarz's reflection principle for unbounded quasidisks.

entry.title: Foward the theory of Sobolev's mappings on the plane
entry.summary: The paper is devoted to the study of homeomoephisms with finite distortion on the plane with use of the modulus techniques.

entry.title: On the Sendov conjecture and the critical points of polynomials
entry.summary: In this paper, we obtain new results on the critical points of a polynomial. We discuss the Sendov conjecture for polynomials of degree nine.

entry.title: Locally CR Spherical Three Manifolds
entry.summary: Every open and orientable three manifold has a CR structure which is locally equivalent to the standard CR structure on $S^3$.

entry.title: A probabilistic proof of the Open Mapping Theorem for analytic functions
entry.summary: The conformal invariance of Brownian motion is used to give a short proof of the Open Mapping Theorem for analytic functions.

entry.title: Rapidly growing entire functions with three singular values
entry.summary: We settle the problem of finding an entire function with three singular values whose Nevanlinna characteristic dominates an arbitrarily prescribed function.

entry.title: The openness conjecture for plurisubharmonic functions
entry.summary: We give a proof of the openness conjecture of Demailly and Koll\'ar.
entry.arxiv:comment: 10 pages. This article supersedes our previous post, 1305.0544, which concerns the case of projective manifolds

entry.title: Derivatives of meromorphic functions of finite order
entry.summary: A result is proved concerning meromorphic functions of finite order in the plane such that all but finitely many zeros of the second derivative are zeros of the first derivative.

entry.title: Some new properties of Jacobi's theta functions
entry.summary: In this paper, a monotonicity property for the quotient of two Jacobi's theta functions with respect to the modulus $k$ is proved.

entry.title: Propagation at the vertex of a sector
entry.summary: We discuss holomorphic extension across a boundary point in terms of sector property. The point is of infinite type and the sector is accordingly "cusped" at the vertex.

entry.title: Regularity of Canonical Operators and Nebenh√ºlle: Hartogs Domains
entry.summary: We relate the regularity of the Bergman projection operator and the canonical solution operator to the Nebenh\"ulle of complete Hartogs domains.

entry.title: A maximum principle for hermitian (and other) metrics
entry.summary: We consider homomorphisms of hermitian holomorphic Hilbert bundles. Assuming the homomorphism decreases curvature, we prove that its pointwise norm is plurisubharmonic.

entry.title: On The Generalized Riemann Hypothesis
entry.summary: The study of the global mapping properties of arbitrary Dirichlet L-functions is undertaken. The results are applied to the proof of the Generalized Riemann Hypothesis.

entry.title: A note on singularity of fibers of singular sets
entry.summary: A general theorem on fibers of singular sets is presented.

entry.title: Sur la th√©orie d'Ahlfors des surfaces
entry.summary: We revisit Ahlfors theory of covering surfaces thanks to Stokes theorem.

entry.title: Strong openness conjecture for plurisubharmonic functions
entry.summary: In this article, we give a proof of the strong openness conjecture for plurisubharmonic functions posed by Demailly.

entry.title: Thomae Formulae for General Fully Ramified $Z_{n}$ Curves
entry.summary: We generalize the elementary methods presented in several examples in the book \cite{[FZ]} to obtain the Thomae formulae for general fully ramified $Z_{n}$ curves.

entry.title: Carleman approximation by holomorphic automorphisms of $\mathbb C^n$
entry.summary: We approximate smooth maps defined on non-compact totally real manifolds by holomorphic automorphisms of $\mathbb C^n$.

entry.title: On Caratheodory Completeness in C^n
entry.summary: We study c-completeness on domains in C^n. We reprove Sibony/Selby result on completeness on the complex plane. We also give a characterization of c-completeness in Reinhardt domains.

entry.title: On finite lipschitz Orlicz Sobolev classes
entry.summary: It is found a sufficient condition of finite Lipschitz of homeomorphisms of the Orlicz-Sobolev class under a condition of the Calderon type.

entry.title: Holomorphic Approximation in Banach Spaces: A survey
entry.summary: We give a survey about the Runge approximation problem for a holomorphic function defined on the unit ball of a complex Banach space.

entry.title: Value sharing by an entire function with its derivatives
entry.summary: We prove a uniqueness theorem for an entire function, which shares certain values with its higher order derivatives.
entry.arxiv:comment: Accepted for publication in Acta Math. Vietnam

entry.title: Quasi-isometries in strongly convex domains
entry.summary: We provide examples of quasi-isometries for strongly convex domains in $\mathbb C^n$ endowed with their Kobayashi distance.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:1202.4985

entry.title: Decay Rates for Cusp Functions
entry.summary: We make some observations on the decay rates of the Fourier coefficients of cusp functions.

entry.title: M. Riesz-Schur-type inequalities for entire functions of exponential type
entry.summary: We prove a general M. Riesz-Schur-type inequality for entire functions of exponential type.

entry.title: The Jacobian Conjecture for the space of all the inner functions
entry.summary: We prove the Jacobian Conjecture for the space of all the inner functions in the unit disc.

entry.title: Distribution of zeros of polynomials with positive coefficients
entry.summary: We describe the limit zero distributions of sequences of polynomials with positive coefficients.

entry.title: Uniqueness of Gabor series
entry.summary: We prove that any complete and minimal Gabor system of Gaussians is a Markushevich basis in $L^2(\mathbb{R})$.

entry.title: Distortion and covering theorems of pluriharmonic mappings
entry.summary: In this paper, we mainly investigate distortion and covering theorems on some classes of pluriharmonic mappings.

entry.title: Pavlovic's theorem in space
entry.summary: We study higher dimensional counterparts to the well-known theorem of Pavlovic \cite{pa3}, that every harmonic quasiconformal mapping of the disk is bi-Lipschitz.

entry.title: Littlewood subordination principle for proper holomorphic functions
entry.summary: We generalize Littlewood subordination principle for proper holomorphic functions and give many applications.

entry.title: On the regularity of CR mappings between CR manifolds of hypersurface type
entry.summary: We prove smooth and analytic versions of the classical Schwarz reflection principle for transversal CR mappings between two CR manifolds of hypersurface type.

entry.title: Nilpotent Toeplitz Operators on Reinhardt Domains
entry.summary: We construct explicit examples of non-trivial nilpotent Toeplitz operators on Bergman spaces of certain Reinhardt domains in $\mathbb{C}^2$.

entry.title: Existence of common hypercyclic vectors for translation operators
entry.summary: We prove the existence of common hypercyclic, entire functions for certain families of translation operators.

entry.title: Interpolation schemes in weighted Bergman spaces
entry.summary: We extend our work on nonseparated interpolating sequences, originally developed for Bergman spaces with weights of the form $(1 - |z|^2)^\alpha$, to more general weights.

entry.title: A log canonical threshold test
entry.summary: In terms of log canonical threshold, we characterize plurisubharmonic functions with logarithmic asymptotical behaviour.

entry.title: Generalized quasiisometry on smooth riemannian manifolds
entry.summary: We study the boundary behavior of finitely Bi-Lipschitz mappings on smooth Riemannian manifolds

entry.title: On a result by Y. Groman and J. P. Solomon
entry.summary: We give a short proof of a reverse isoperimetric inequality due to Y. Groman and J. P. Solomon.

entry.title: Weierstrass points of superelliptic curves
entry.summary: In this lecture we give a brief introduction to Weierstrass points of curves and computational aspects of $q$-Weierstrass points on superelliptic curves.

entry.title: Abstract basins of attraction
entry.summary: Abstract basins appear naturally in different areas of several complex variables. In this survey we want to describe three different topics in which they play an important role, leading to interesting open problems.

entry.title: La pseudodistance de Caratheodory sur des ouverts emboites
entry.summary: Given two open sets U_1 contained in U_2, we compare the Caratheodory pseudodistance on U_1 and U_2.

entry.title: Schwarz lemma for holomorphic mappings in the unit ball
entry.summary: In this note we establish a Schwarz type inequality for holomorphic mappings between unit balls $B_n$ and $B_m$ in corresponding complex spaces.

entry.title: The asymptotic behavior of solutions of the Beltrami equation at infinity
entry.summary: We study the asymptotic behavior of homeomorphic solutions of the Beltrami equation with different conditions on the dilatation at infinity in this paper.

entry.title: Formal and convergent solutions of analytic equations
entry.summary: We provide the detailed proof of a strengthened version of the M. Artin Approximation Theorem.

entry.title: Problems on extremal decomposition of the complex plane
entry.summary: Considered here is one quite general problem about description of extremal configurations maximizing the product of inner radii non-overlapping domains.

entry.title: Several Complex Variables
entry.summary: These are notes from a basic course in Several Complex Variables

entry.title: On a conjecture by Blocki-Zwonek
entry.summary: The article provides a counterexample to a conjecture by Blocki-Zwonek.

entry.title: Function Theory on Inflationary Tessellations
entry.summary: This paper studies function theory on periodic and aperiodic inflationary tessellations.

entry.title: The Spectrum of Volterra-type integration operators on generalized Fock spaces
entry.summary: We describe the spectrum of certain integration operators acting on general- ized Fock spaces.

entry.title: The Generalization of Schottky Inequality and Its Applications
entry.summary: This article used Bloch function to derive Schottky inequality, obtained its generalization by using elliptic integral deviation function and demonstrated its applications.

entry.title: Fatou's interpolation theorem implies the Rudin-Carleson theorem
entry.summary: The purpose of this paper is to show that the Rudin-Carleson interpolation theorem is a direct corollary of Fatou's much older interpolation theorem (of 1906).

entry.title: On the representation of a polynmial as a sum of mononomials
entry.summary: We discuss various aspects of representation of a polynomial as a sum of monomials (for example, uniqueness of such representation and related estimations).

entry.title: On a lower bound of the Kobayashi metric
entry.summary: It is shown that a lower bound of the Kobayashi metric of convex domains in C^n does not hold for non-convex domains.

entry.title: Remarks on trigonometric functions after Eisenstein
entry.summary: We modify the Whittaker-Watson account of the Eisenstein approach to the trigonometric functions, basing these functions independently on the Eisenstein function $\varepsilon_2$.

entry.title: Open Whitney umbrellas are locally polynomially convex
entry.summary: It is proved that any smooth open Whitney umbrella in $\mathbb C^2$ is locally polynomially convex near the singular point.

entry.title: Positive neighborhoods of rational curves
entry.summary: We study neighborhoods of rational curves in surfaces with self-intersection number 1 that can be linearised.

entry.title: Superharmonicity of Logarithm of Jacobian of harmonic mappings between surfaces
entry.summary: We prove that the Logarithm of the Jacobian of a sense preserving harmonic mappings between surfaces is superharmonic, provided that the Gaussian curvature of the image domain is non-negative.

entry.title: Neville's primitive elliptic functions: the case ${\bf g_3 = 0}$
entry.summary: The vanishing of the invariant $g_3$ attached to a lattice $\Lambda$ singles out a midpoint lattice and yields a square-root of the associated Weierstrass function $\wp_{\Lambda}$.

entry.title: Analytic adjoint ideal sheaves associated to plurisubharmonic functions
entry.summary: In this article, we will present that the analytic adjoint ideal sheaves associated to plurisubharmonic functions are not coherent.

entry.title: An irreducibility criterion for power series
entry.summary: We prove an irreducibility criterion for polynomials with power series coefficients generalizing previous known results concerning quasi-ordinary polynomials.

entry.title: Orthogonality of divisorial Zariski decompositions for classes with volume zero
entry.summary: We show that the orthogonality conjecture for divisorial Zariski decompositions on compact Kahler manifolds holds for pseudoeffective (1,1) classes with volume zero.

entry.title: Equilateral triangle skew condition for quasiconformality
entry.summary: We characterize quasiconformal mappings in terms of the distortion of the vertices of equilateral triangles.

entry.title: Some Remarks on Quasinearly Subharmonic Functions
entry.summary: We prove some basic properties of quasinearly subharmonic functions and quasinearly subharmonic functions in the narrow sense.

entry.title: Uniqueness Properties of Hardy Space Functions
entry.summary: We study boundary uniqueness properties of Hardy space functions in several complex variables. Along the way, we develop properties of the Lumer Hardy space.

entry.title: Residual Cauchy-type formula on Riemann surfaces
entry.summary: We construct a Cauchy type formula on open subdomains of Riemann surfaces

entry.title: Cartan Theorems for Stein manifolds over a discrete valuation base
entry.summary: In this paper we prove Cartan theorems A and B for Stein manifolds over certain discrete valuation rings.

entry.title: The range of a real Smirnov function
entry.summary: We give a characterization of the ranges of real Smirnov functions. In addition, we discuss the valence of such functions.

entry.title: Interpolating sequences on the bidisk
entry.summary: We give a characterization of interpolating sequences for bounded analytic functions on the bidisk.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: International Journal of Mathematics, Vol. 12 No. 9 [2001] 1103-1114

entry.title: The three point Pick problem on the Bidisk
entry.summary: We analyze the three point Pick interpolation problem on the bidisk
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: New York Journal of Mathematics Vol. 6 [2000] 227-236

entry.title: On matrix generalization of Robinson's Energy Delay Theorem
entry.summary: An elementary proof of Robinson's Energy Delay Theorem on minimum-phase functions is presented. The proof is generalized to the matrix case as well.

entry.title: A geometric second main theorem
entry.summary: We prove a truncated second main theorem in the projective plane for entire curves which cluster on an algebraic curve.

entry.title: Tian's invariant of the Grassmann manifold
entry.summary: We prove that Tian's invariant on the complex Grassmann manifold $G_{p, q}(\mathbb{C})$ is equal to $1/(p+q)$.

entry.title: A disproof of a conjecture of Al Baernstein II
entry.summary: We answer a question that was asked by Albert Baernstein II, regarding the coefficients of circular symmetrization. The conjecture is not true generically.

entry.title: Holomorphic motions and complex geometry
entry.summary: We show that the graph of a holomorphic motion of the unit disc cannot be biholomorphic to a strongly pseudoconvex domain in C n .

entry.title: On the removable singularities of complex analytic sets
entry.summary: There is proved the sufficiency of several conditions for the removability of singularities of complex-analytic sets in domains of $\mathbb C^n$.

entry.title: Bounds on Distance to Variety in Terms of Coefficients of Bivariate Polynomials
entry.summary: A short note on bounds on distance to variety of a point in terms of the Taylor coefficients at the point.

entry.title: Invariance of Diederich-Fornaess index
entry.summary: We show that the Diederich-Fornaess index of a domain in a Stein manifold is invariant under CR-diffeomorphisms. For this purpose we also improve CR-extension theorem.

entry.title: On Picard Value Problem of Some Difference Polynomials
entry.summary: In this paper, we study the value distribution of zeros of certain nonlinear difference polynomials of entire functions of finite order.

entry.title: Singularities of local Ahlfors currents
entry.summary: We prove that a complex curve charged by a local Ahlfors current is either a disc or an annulus.

entry.title: $L^p$-norm estimate of the Bergman projection on the Hartogs triangle
entry.summary: The purpose of this paper is to give an estimate of the $L^p$-norm of the Bergman projection on the Hartogs triangle.

entry.title: Analytic Capacity : computation and related problems
entry.summary: We present a brief introduction to analytic capacity, with an emphasis on its numerical computation. We also discuss several related open problems.

entry.title: Uniformization and Steinness
entry.summary: It is shown that the unit ball in ${\mathbb C}^n$ is the only complex manifold that can universally cover both Stein and non-Stein strictly pseudoconvex domains.

entry.title: New Characterizations of Algebraic Regularity
entry.summary: In this paper, we give new characterizations of algebraic regularity by using differential forms and difference quotients.

entry.title: Estimations of the Bergman kernel of the punctured disk
entry.summary: We give estimations of the Bergman kernel on the punctured disk with the standard complete Poincare metric.

entry.title: Infinite Product of Bicomplex Numbers
entry.summary: In this article the infinite product of bicomplex numbers is defined and the convergence and divergence of this product are discussed.

entry.title: Bicomplex Mobius Transformation
entry.summary: In this article the bicomplex version of Mobius transformation is defined and special attention is paid to find the fixed points of a bicomplex Mobius transformation.

entry.title: Pauli operators and the d-bar-Neumann problem
entry.summary: We apply methods from complex analysis, in particular the d-bar-Neumann operator, to investigate spectral properties of Pauli operators.

entry.title: A note on Schwarz lemma for the tetrablock
entry.summary: We present an extended version of a Schwarz lemma for the tetrablock by Abouhajar, White and Young.

entry.title: Minimal surfaces and Schwarz lemma
entry.summary: We prove a sharp Schwarz type inequality for the Weierstrass-Enneper representation of the minimal surfaces.

entry.title: A uniform boundedness principle in pluripotential theory
entry.summary: For families of continuous plurisubharmonic functions we show that, in a local sense, separately bounded above implies bounded above.

entry.title: Lelong numbers and vector bundles
entry.summary: We study Lelong numbers and integrability indices for $S^1$-invariant singular metrics on vector bundles over the disk.
entry.arxiv:comment: Dedicated to the memory of G.M. Henkin. In Journal of Geometric Analysis , 'online first'

entry.title: The norm of the harmonic Bergman projection and Besov space
entry.summary: We estimate the norm of the harmonic Bergman projection in the context of harmonic Besov spaces. We obtain the two-side norm estimates in general Lp-case.

entry.title: On transversely holomorphic foliations with homogeneous transverse structure
entry.summary: In this paper we study transversely holomorphic foliations of complex codimension one with some hypothesis on the transverse structure.

entry.title: Complex Neumann Problem and Kohn's Algorithm
entry.summary: This article gives a rapid introduction to the complex Neumann problem and Kohn's algorithm for generating subelliptic estimate.

entry.title: Th√©or√®me de Hartogs-Bochner dans $P_2(\mathbb{C})$
entry.summary: The present paper have been replaced by the paper: Hartogs-Bochner type theorem in Projective Space (math.CV/0011095) in which we prove the following Hartogs-Bochner type theorem: Let $M$ be a connected $C^2$ hypersurface of $P_n(\mathbb{C})$ ($n\geq 2$) which divides $P_n(\mathbb{C})$ in two connected open sets $\Omega_1$ and $\Omega_2$. Then there exists $i \in \{1,2\}$ such that $C^{1}$ CR functions defined on $M$ extends holomorphically to $\Omega_i$.
entry.arxiv:comment: The present paper have been replaced by the paper: Hartogs-Bochner type theorem in Projective Space (math.CV/0011095)

entry.title: Polynomial hulls and an optimization problem
entry.summary: Let T be the unit circle in the complex plane C. This paper proves the existence of analytic structure in a compact subset K of T X C^n, where K has so-called "lineally convex" or "hypoconvex" fibers over T. It also addresses a related H-infinity optimization problem. The theorems here remove a number of unnatural assumptions required in an earlier work by the same author, "Polynomial hulls and H-infinity control for a hypoconvex constraint." (See http://www.arxiv.org/abs/math.CV/0001039)
entry.arxiv:comment: 12 pages. To appear in the Journal of Geometric Analysis. This work is the sequel to another paper by the same author, (see http://www.arxiv.org/abs/math.CV/0001039) "Polynomial hulls and H-infinity control for a hypoconvex constraint."

entry.title: Quaternionic plurisubharmonic functions and their applications to convexity
entry.summary: The goal of this article is to present a survey of the recent theory of plurisubharmonic functions of quaternionic variables, and its applications to theory of valuations on convex sets and HKT-geometry (HyperK\"ahler with Torsion). The exposition follows the articles math.CV/0104209, math.CV/0208005, math.MG/0401219 by the author and math.CV/0510140 by M. Verbitsky and the author.
entry.arxiv:comment: 17 pages. The definition of quaternionic Hessian is replaced with a transposed matrix as it should be

entry.title: On the Removable Singularities for Meromorphic Mappings
entry.summary: If E is a nonempty closed subset of the locally finite Hausdorff (2n-2)-measure on an n-dimensional complex manifold M and all points of E are nonremovable for a meromorphic mapping of M \ E into a compact K\"ahler manifold, then E is a pure (n-1)-dimensional complex analytic subset of M.

entry.title: Zero sets of some classes of entire functions
entry.summary: A method of constructing an entire function with given zeros and estimates of growth is suggested. It gives a possibility to describe zero sets of certain classes of entire functions of one and several variables in terms of growth of volume of these sets in certain polycylinders.

entry.title: A counterexample to the Arakelyan Conjecture
entry.summary: A ``self--similar'' example is constructed that shows that a conjecture of N. U. Arakelyan on the order of decrease of deficiencies of an entire function of finite order is not true.

entry.title: Cartwright-type and Bernstein-type theorems for functions analytic in a cone
entry.summary: Cartwright-type and Bernstein-type theorems, previously known only for functions of exponential type in $\C^n$, are extended to the case of functions of arbitrary order in a cone.

entry.title: The Kobayashi metric for non-convex complex ellipsoids
entry.summary: In the paper we give some necessary conditions for a mapping to be a $\kappa$-geodesic in non-convex complex ellipsoids. Using these results we calculate explicitly the Kobayashi metric in the ellipsoids $\{|z_1|^2+|z_2|^{2m}<1\}\subset\bold C^2$, where $m<\frac12$.

entry.title: Propagation of Gevrey Regularity for a Class of Hypoelliptic Equations
entry.summary: We prove results on the propagation of Gevrey and analytic wave front sets for a class of $C^\infty$ hypoelliptic equations with double characteristics.

entry.title: The Lu Qi-Keng Conjecture Fails Generically
entry.summary: The bounded domains of holomorphy in~$\mathbf{C}^n$ whose Bergman kernel functions are zero-free form a nowhere dense subset (with respect to a variant of the Hausdorff distance) of all bounded domains of holomorphy.

entry.title: Reinhardt Domains with Non-Compact Automorphism Groups
entry.summary: We give an explicit description of smoothly bounded Reinhardt domains with noncompact automorphism groups. In particular, this description confirms a special case of a conjecture of Greene/Krantz.

entry.title: Finite Type Conditions on Reinhardt Domains
entry.summary: In this paper we prove that, if $p$ is a boundary point of a smoothly bounded pseudoconvex Reinhardt domain in $\C^n$, then the variety type at $p$ is identical to the regular type.

entry.title: Regularity of Holomorphic Correspondences and Applications to the Mapping Problems
entry.summary: We study the regularity results of holomorphic correspondences. As an application, we combine it with certain recently developed methods to obtain the extension theorem for proper holomorphic mappings between domains with real analytic boundaries in the complex 2-space.

entry.title: An Example of a Domain with Non-Compact Automorphism Group
entry.summary: We give an example of a bounded, pseudoconvex, circular domain in ${\mathbb C}^3$ with smooth, real-analytic boundary and non-compact automorphism group, which is not biholomorphically equivalent to any Reinhardt domain.

entry.title: Effective formulas for invariant functions -- case of elementary Reinhardt domains
entry.summary: In the paper we find effective formulas for the invariant functions, appearing in the theory of several complex variables, of the elementary Reinhardt domains. This gives us the first example of a large family of domains for which the functions are calculated explicitly.

entry.title: Global regularity of the dbar-Neumann problem: a survey of the L^2-Sobolev theory
entry.summary: This is a survey article written for the proceedings of the special year in several complex variables, 1995-1996, at the Mathematical Sciences Research Institute in Berkeley.

entry.title: Plurisubharmonic functions and subellipticity of the dbar-Neumann problem on nonsmooth domains
entry.summary: We show subellipticity of the d-bar Neumann problem on domains with Lipschitz boundary in the presence of plurisubharmonic functions with Hessians of algebraic growth. In particular, a subelliptic estimate holds near a point where the boundary is piecewise smooth of finite type.

entry.title: Some applications of the Kohn-Rossi extension theorems
entry.summary: We prove extension results for meromorphic functions by combining the Kohn-Rossi extension theorems with Andreotti's theory on the algebraic and analytic dependence of meromorphic functions on pseudoconcave manifolds. Versions of Kohn-Rossi theorems for pseudoconvex domains are included.

entry.title: Complex Plateau problem in non K√§hler manifolds
entry.summary: We consider a complex Plateau problem for strongly pseudoconvex contours in non K\"ahler manifolds. A positive solution in the case of manifolds carrying a pluriclosed Hermitian metric forms is given. For the general case we propose a conjecture.

entry.title: A moduli space of non-compact curves on a complex surface
entry.summary: We show that under mild boundary conditions the moduli space of non-compact curves on a complex surface is (locally) an analytic subset of a ball in a Banach manifold, defined by {\it finitely} many holomorphic function.

entry.title: On partial analyticity of CR mappings
entry.summary: We study the problem of holomorphic extension of a smooth CR mapping from a real analytic hypersurface to a real algebraic set in complex spaces of different dimensions.

entry.title: Vita: Friedrich Wilhelm Wiener
entry.summary: We report on the life and work of F. Wiener, whom we confused with N. Wiener in a previous article.

entry.title: Analytic continuation of a biholomorphic mapping
entry.summary: We present a new proof of Pinchuk's theorem on the analytic continuation of a biholomorphic mapping from a strongly pseudoconvex analytic real hypersurface to a compact strongly pseudoconvex analytic real hypersurface in a complex euclidean space.

entry.title: Matrix-Valued Corona Theorem for Multiply Connected Domains
entry.summary: Let $D\subset\Co$ be a bounded domain, whose boundary $B$ consists of $k$ simple closed continuous curves and $H^{\infty}(D)$ be the algebra of bounded analytic functions on $D$. We prove the matrix-valued corona theorem for matrices with entries in $H^{\infty}(D)$.

entry.title: A reflection principle for real-analytic submanifolds of complex spaces
entry.summary: We give an invariant nondegeneracy condition for CR--maps between generic submanifolds in different dimensions and use it to prove a reflection principle for these maps.

entry.title: Note on double reflection and algebraicity of holomorphic mappings
entry.summary: In this note, our purpose is to establish shortly the algebraicity of a holomorphic mapping between real algebraic CR manifolds under a double reflection condition which generalizes the classical single reflection. A complete study of various double reflection conditions is also provided.

entry.title: Traces of Subharmonic Functions to Fractal Sets
entry.summary: We study traces of a class of subharmonic functions to Ahlfors regular subsets of $\Co^{n}$. In particular, we establish for the traces a generalized BMO-property and the reverse H\"{o}lder inequality.

entry.title: On the commuting polynomial endomorphisms of {C}^2
entry.summary: We determine all couples of commuting polynomial endomorphisms of C^2 that extends to holomorphic endomorphisms of P^2 and that have disjoint sequences of iterates.

entry.title: Compactness in the d-bar-Neumann problem
entry.summary: This paper surveys the theory of compactness of the d-bar-Neumann problem. It also contains several results which improve upon what was previously known.

entry.title: Domains of holomorphy with edges and lower dimensional boundary singularities
entry.summary: Necessary and sufficient geometric conditions are given for domains with regular boundary points and edges to be domains of holomorphy provided the remainder boundary subset is of zero Hausdorff 1-codimensional measure.

entry.title: Segre varieties and Lie symmetries
entry.summary: Using the classical S.Lie method we obtain a complete description of infinitesimal symmetries of a holomorphic PDE system defining the Segre family of a real analytic hypersurface. This gives a new proof of some well known results of CR geometry.

entry.title: Good Stein Neighborhood Bases and Regularity of the d-bar Neumann Problem
entry.summary: We show that if the closure of a smooth pseudoconvex domain admits a "sufficiently nice" Stein neighborhood basis, then the d-bar Neumann problem on the domain is globally regular.

entry.title: An example concerning Bergman completeness
entry.summary: We construct a bounded plane domain which is Bergman complete but for which the Bergman kernel does not tend to infinity as the point approaches the boundary.
entry.arxiv:comment: 10 pages, to be published in Nagoya Math. J

entry.title: Singular Monge-Ampere foliations
entry.summary: This replaces the previous version, by correcting an error in the proof of Theorem 1.4, that was pointed out by the referee.

entry.title: Singularities of plurisubharmonic functions and positive closed currents
entry.summary: This is a survey of results, both classical and recent, on behaviour of plurisubharmonic functions near their $-\infty$-points, together with the related topics for positive closed currents.
entry.arxiv:comment: 45 pages; a slightly extended and updated version

entry.title: A strong uniqueness theorem for planar vector fields
entry.summary: This work establishes a strong uniqueness property for a class of planar locally integrable vector fields. A result on pointwise convergence to the boundary value is also proved for bounded solutions.

entry.title: Hilbert C*-modules are JB*-triples
entry.summary: We show that every Hilbert C*-module E is a JB*-triple in a canonical way and establish an explicit expression for the holomorphic automorphisms of the unit ball of E.

entry.title: Holomorphic extension of smooth CR-mappings between real-analytic and real-algebraic CR-manifolds
entry.summary: We establish results on holomorphic extension of CR-mappings of class $C^\infty$ between a real-analytic CR-submanifold of $\C^N$ and a real-algebraic CR-submanifold of $\C^{N'}$.

entry.title: The Bergman kernel on the intersection of two balls in C^2
entry.summary: We obtain an asymptotic expansion and some regularity results for the Bergman kernel on the intersection of two balls in C^2.

entry.title: Realizing Connected Lie Groups As Automorphism Groups Of Complex Manifolds
entry.summary: We show that every connected real Lie group can be realized as the full automorphism group of a Stein hyperbolic complex manifold.

entry.title: Dimension of pluriharmonic measure and polynomial endomorphisms of $\C^n$
entry.summary: Let $F$ be a polynomial endomorphism of $\C^n$ which extends holomorphically to $\P^n$. We prove that the dimension of $\mu_F$, the pluriharmonic measure on the boundary of the filled Julia set of $F$, is bounded above by $2n-1$.

entry.title: Study of a functional equation associated to the Kummer's equation of the trilogarihtm. Applications
entry.summary: In this paper we study a functional equation associated to the Kummer's equation (K) of the trilogarithm. Then we apply our results to web geometry and to characterize the functions solution of (K).

entry.title: A Morera type theorem in the strip
entry.summary: We prove the following result. Let f be a continuous function in the closed infinite strip in complex plane. Suppose the restriction of f to every circle inscribed in the strip extends holomorphically inside the circle. Then f is holomorphic in the open strip.

entry.title: Sur la laminarite de certains courants
entry.summary: We show that a sequence of smooth analytic curves of the unit ball of the complex plane, for which the genus is bounded by the area, converges to a lamination in a weak sense.

entry.title: On extremal holomorphically contractible families
entry.summary: We prove that the category of generalized holomorphically contractible families possesses maximal and minimal objects. Moreover, we present basic properties of these extremal families.

entry.title: Foliations on complex projective surfaces
entry.summary: These are lecture notes of a course given in Pisa, SNS, in february 2002. They provide a classification of holomorphic foliations of nongeneral type on compact Kaehler surfaces.

entry.title: Positive trigonometric polynomials
entry.summary: We study the boundary of the nonnegative trigonometric polynomials from the algebraic point of view. In particularly, we show that it is a subset of an irreducible algebraic hypersurface and established its explicit form in terms of resultants.

entry.title: Pluripolar graphs are holomorphic
entry.summary: We prove that the graph of a continuous function $f$, defined on a domain of ${\mathbb C}^n$, is pluripolar if and only if $f$ is holomorphic.

entry.title: Functions of several quaternion variables and quaternion manifolds
entry.summary: Functions of several quaternion variables are investigated and integral representation theorems for them are proved. With the help of them solutions of the $\tilde \partial $-equations are studied. Moreover, quaternion Stein manifolds are defined and investigated.

entry.title: Introductory Clifford Analysis
entry.summary: This paper is an elaboration of an introductory talk given by the author at a workshop on Clifford algebras at Tennessee Technical University, in May 2002. We give an introduction to the basic concepts of Clifford analysis, including links to harmonic analysis, Fourier analysis and conformally flat manifolds.

entry.title: Mappings between real submanifolds in complex space
entry.summary: In this paper I survey some recent results on finite determination, convergence, and approximation of formal mappings between real submanifolds in complex spaces. A number of conjectures are also given.
entry.arxiv:comment: 15 pages; dedicated to Robert Greene on his 60th birthday

entry.title: Wong-Rosay Theorem in almost complex manifolds
entry.summary: We study the compactness of sequences of diffeomorphisms in almost complex manifolds in terms of the direct images of the standard integrable structure.

entry.title: Meromorphic functions with three singular values
entry.summary: The minimal possible rate of growth of a meromorphic function with three critical values is found.

entry.title: On Valiron's Theorem
entry.summary: This is a survey on Valiron's Theorem about the convergence properties of orbits of analytic self-maps of the disk of hyperbolic type and related questions in one and several variables.

entry.title: Interpolation in $\hat{\E^\prime}(\R)$
entry.summary: We give a geometric description of the interpolating varieties for the algebra of Fourier transforms of distributions (or Beurling ultradistributions) with compact support on the real line.

entry.title: On automorphisms of the symmetrized bidisc
entry.summary: We characterize the group $\operatorname{Aut}(\mathbb G_2)$ for the symmetrized bidisc $\mathbb G_2:=\{(\lambda_1+\lambda_2,\lambda_1\lambda_2):|\lambda_1|,|\lambda_2|<1\}\sub set\mathbb C^2$.

entry.title: Logarithmic Comparison Theorem and Euler homogeneity for free divisors
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn by the author since the proof of Lemma 8 is not correct.

entry.title: Semiglobal results for $\bar\partial$ on a complex space with arbitrary singularities
entry.summary: We obtain some $L^2$ results for the Cauchy-Riemann operator on forms that vanish to high order near the singular set of a complex space.

entry.title: Non-autonomous dynamics of holomorphic mappings in projective space
entry.summary: We study the dynamics of compositions of a sequence of holomorphic mappings in projective space. We define ergodicity and mixing for non-autonomous dynamical systems, and we construct totally invariant measures for which our sequence satisfies these properties.

entry.title: Intrinsic capacities on compact K√§hler manifolds
entry.summary: We study fine properties of quasiplurisubharmonic functions on compact K\"ahler manifolds. We define and study several intrinsic capacities which characterize pluripolar sets and show that locally pluripolar sets are globally "quasi-pluripolar".

entry.title: Geometry of the symmetrized polydisc
entry.summary: We describe all proper holomorphic mappings of the symmetrized polydisc and study its geometric properties. We also apply the obtained results to the study of the spectral unit ball in $\MM_n(\CC^n)$.

entry.title: Equivalence of the Bergman and Teichmuller metrics on Teichmuller spaces
entry.summary: We prove that the Bergman and the Teichmuller metrics are equivalent on Teichmuller spaces.
entry.arxiv:comment: A serious mistake in the previous manuscript was corrected

entry.title: Hearing pseudoconvexity with the Kohn Laplacian
entry.summary: A bounded domain in several complex variables with connected Lipschitz boundary is pseudoconvex if and only if the bottom of the (essential) spectrum of the Kohn Laplacian is positive on all (0, q)-forms with square-integrable coefficients.

entry.title: An Example related to Brody's theorem
entry.summary: We discuss an example related to the method of Brody. The example is an open subset of a compact complex torus which is covered by entire curves, but not by Brody curves.

entry.title: On non-integrable complex distributions: an approach by transversality with real domains
entry.summary: We study the classification of singularities of holomorphic foliations and non-integrable one-forms under the hypothesis of transversality with real hypersurfaces.

entry.title: The Maximum Principle for the Bergman Space and the M√∂bius Pseudodistance for the Annulus
entry.summary: It is shown that the formula for the M\"obius pseudodistance for the annulus yields better estimates than previously known for the constant in the Bergman space maximum principle. A maximum principle for the Fock space is proved.

entry.title: Alguns fenomens de continuaci√≥ analit√≠ca en una variable complexa
entry.summary: In this paper we examinate some phenomena arising when a holomorphic germ is analytically continued.
entry.arxiv:comment: Expository paper. Please note that the author is known as "Claudi Meneghin" too

entry.title: Subextension of plurisubharmonic functions with weak singularities
entry.summary: We prove several results showing that plurisubharmonic functions with various bounds on their Monge-Ampere masses on a bounded hyperconvex domain always admit global plurisubharmonic subextension with logarithmic growth at infinity.

entry.title: The multipole Lempert function is monotone under inclusion of pole sets
entry.summary: We prove the the multipole Lempert function is monotone under inclusion of pole sets.

entry.title: Subanalytic sets and complex analytic geometry
entry.summary: We consider a subanalytic subset A of a complex analytic manifold M (when M is viewed as a real manifold) and formulate conditions under which A is a complex analytic subset of M.

entry.title: Coarse equidistribution of the argument of entire functions of finite order
entry.summary: We present several results that show somewhat surprising equidistribution patterns in the asymptotic behaviour of the argument of entire functions of finite order.

entry.title: Laminations dans les espaces projectifs complexes
entry.summary: In this work, we extend K. Kodaira's embedding theorem to non compact hermitian complex manifolds and laminations by complex manifolds.

entry.title: Asymptotics of zeros for some entire functions
entry.summary: We study the asymptotics of zeros for entire functions of the form \sin z + \int_{-1}^1 f(t)e^{izt}dt with f belonging to a space X \hookrightarrow L_1(-1,1) possessing some minimal regularity properties.

entry.title: Inegalites de Markov tangentielles locales sur les courbes algebriques singulieres de R^n
entry.summary: We prove that all real singular algebraic curves admits Markov's local tangential inequalities. We give a geometric significance of Markov's exponent.

entry.title: Stone-Weierstrass Theorem
entry.summary: It will be shown that the Stone-Weierstrass theorem for Clifford-valued functions is true for the case of even dimension. It remains valid for the odd dimension if we add a stability condition by principal automorphism.

entry.title: Pseudoholomorphic discs attached to CR-submanifolds of almost complex spaces
entry.summary: Let E be a generic real submanifold of an almost complex manifold. The geometry of Bishop discs attached to E is studied in terms of the Levi form of E.

entry.title: Graphs with multiple sheeted pluripolar hulls
entry.summary: In this paper we study the pluripolar hulls of analytic sets. In particular, we show that hulls of graphs of analytic functions can be multiple sheeted and sheets can be separated by a set of zero dimension.

entry.title: A remark on sums of squares of complex vector fields
entry.summary: This note is a comment on a recent paper by J. J. Kohn. We give an example of a second order partial differential operator, expressed as a sum of squares of complex vector fields satisfying the bracket condition, that is not hypoelliptic.

entry.title: Boundary Nevanlinna--Pick interpolation problems for generalized Schur functions
entry.summary: Three boundary Nevanlinna-Pick interpolation problems at finitely many points are formulated for generalized Schur functions. For each problem, the set of all solutions is parametrized in terms of a linear fractional transformation with a Schur class parameter.

entry.title: On Holomorphic L_{2} functions on Coverings of Strongly Pseudoconvex Manifolds
entry.summary: In this paper we prove an extension of a result of Gromov, Henkin and Shubin [GHS] on holomorphic L_{2} functions on coverings of strongly pseudoconvex manifolds.

entry.title: Spectrum of the d-bar-Neumann Laplacian on polydiscs
entry.summary: The spectrum of the d-bar-Neumann Laplacian on a polydisc in several complex variables is explicitly computed. The calculation exhibits that the spectrum consists of eigenvalues, some of which, in particular the smallest ones, are of infinite multiplicity.

entry.title: A Robin formula for the Fekete-Leja transfinite diameter
entry.summary: This note gives a higher-dimensional generalization of the classical formula cap(K) = exp(-V(E)) expressing the logarithmic capacity in terms of the residue at infinity of its Green's function. The proof uses arithmetic intersection theory.

entry.title: An embedding theorem for pseudoconvex domains in Banach spaces
entry.summary: We show that a pseudoconvex open subset of a Banach space with an unconditional basis is biholomorphic to a closed direct submanifold of a Banach space with an unconditional basis.

entry.title: Semistable points with respect to real forms
entry.summary: We consider actions of real Lie subgroups G of complex reductive Lie groups on Kaehlerian spaces. Our main result is the openness of the set of semistable points with respect to a momentum map and the action of G.

entry.title: Permutable entire functions satisfying algebraic differential equations
entry.summary: It is shown that if two transcendental entire functions permute, and if one of them satisfies an algebraic differential equation, then so does the other one.

entry.title: On Manifolds with trivial logarithmic tangent bundle: The non-Kaehler case
entry.summary: We study non-Kaehler manifolds with trivial logarithmic tangent bundle. We show that each such manifold arises as a fiber bundle with a compact complex parallelizable manifold as basis and a toric variety as fiber.

entry.title: The Bergman kernel of the symmetrized polydisc in higher dimensions has zeros
entry.summary: We prove that the Bergman kernel of the symmetrized polydisc in dimension greater than two has zeros.

entry.title: On the uniqueness of classical semiconjugations for self-maps of the disk
entry.summary: We study the uniqueness properties of classical semiconjugations for analytic self-maps of the disk, by characterizing them as canonical solutions to certain functional equations. As a corollary, we obtain a complete description of all possible solutions to such equations.

entry.title: Covering and distortion theorems for spirallike functions with respect to a boundary point
entry.summary: In this note we obtain some distortion results for spirallike functions with respect to a boundary point. In particular, we find the maximal domain covered by all spirallike functions of order $\beta$.

entry.title: The pluri-fine topology is locally connected
entry.summary: We prove that the pluri-fine topology on any open set $\Omega$ in $\mathbb{C}^{n}$ is locally connected. This answers a question by Fuglede in [4]. See also Bedford [6].

entry.title: The Lempert function of the symmetrized polydisc in higher dimensions is not a distance
entry.summary: We prove that the Lempert function of the symmetrized polydisc in dimension greater than two is not a distance.

entry.title: Embedding Riemann Surfaces Properly into $\CC^2$
entry.summary: For certain bordered submanifolds $M\subset\CC^2$ we show that $M$ can be embedded properly and holomorphically into $\CC^2$. An application is that any subset of a torus with two boundary components can be embedded properly into $\CC^2$.

entry.title: On the definition of the Kobayashi-Buseman pseudometric
entry.summary: We prove that the $(2n-1)$-th Kobayashi pseudometric of any domain $D\subset\Bbb C^n$ coincides with the Kobayashi--Buseman pseudometric of $D,$ and that $2n-1$ is the optimal number, in general.

entry.title: Diffeomorphisms of Stein structures
entry.summary: We prove that a pseudoholomorphic diffeomorphism between two almost complex manifolds with boundaries satisfying some pseudoconvexity type condition cannot map a pseudoholomorphic disc in the boundary to a single point. This can be viewed as an almost complex analogue of a well-known theorem of J. E. Fornaess.

entry.title: On the boundary behavior of the holomorphic sectional curvature of the Bergman metric
entry.summary: We obtain a conceptually new differential geometric proof of P.F. Klembeck's result that the holomorphic sectional curvature of a strictly pseudoconvex domain approaches (in the boundary limit) the constant sectional curvature of the Bergman metric of the unit ball.

entry.title: Note on the paper of Fu and Wong on strictly pseudoconvex domains with K√§hler--Einstein Bergman metrics
entry.summary: It is shown that the Ramadanov conjecture implies the Cheng conjecture. In particular it follows that the Cheng conjecture holds in dimension two.

entry.title: Pull-back of currents by holomorphic maps
entry.summary: We define the pull-back operator, associated to a meromorphic transform, on several types of currents. We also give a simple proof to a version of a classical theorem on the extension of currents.

entry.title: On holomorphic curves in algebraic torus
entry.summary: We study entire holomorphic curves in the algebraic torus, and show that they can be characterized by the ``growth rate'' of their derivatives.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Journal of Mathematics of Kyoto University, 47-4 (2007), 881-892

entry.title: A Markov-type inequality for arbitrary plane continua
entry.summary: A version of Markov's estimate for the derivative of a polynomial is proved with the interval [-1,1] replaced by an arbitrary continuum in the complex plane.

entry.title: A note on composition operators on Hardy spaces of the polydisk
entry.summary: In this work, we prove that weak compactness of composition operator on $H^{1}(U^{n})$ coincides with its compactness. We also characterize bounded and compact composition operators on $H^{1}(U^{n}).$\

entry.title: Extension of holomorphic maps between real hypersurfaces of different dimension
entry.summary: It is proved that the germ of a holomorphic map from a real analytic hypersurface M in C^n into a strictly pseudoconvex compact real algebraic hypersurface M' in C^N, 1 < n < N extends holomorphically along any path on M.

entry.title: Complements of rationally convex sets
entry.summary: The main objective of this paper is to show that the complement of a rational convex set in $\mathbb{C}^n$ is (n-2)-connected for n>2.

entry.title: Hartogs' theorem on separate holomorphicity for projective spaces
entry.summary: If a mapping of several complex variables into projective space is holomorphic in each pair of variables, then it is globally holomorphic.

entry.title: A Julia--Carath√©odory theorem for hyperbolically monotone mappings in the Hilbert ball
entry.summary: We establish a Julia--Carath\'eodory theorem and a boundary Schwarz--Wolff lemma for hyperbolically monotone mappings in the open unit ball of a complex Hilbert space

entry.title: Attracting divisors on projective algebraic varieties
entry.summary: We obtain sufficient and necessary conditions (in terms of positive singular metrics on an associated line bundle) for a positive divisor $D$ on a projective algebraic variety $X$ to be attracting for a holomorphic map $f:X \mapsto X$.

entry.title: Boundary Nevanlinna-Pick interpolation for generalized Nevanlinna functions
entry.summary: We formulate three boundary Nevanlinna-Pick interpolation problems for generalized Nevanlinna functions. For each problem, we parameterize the set of all solutions in terms of a linear fractional transformation with an extended Nevanlinna class parameter.

entry.title: The Edge of the Wedge Theorem for Tempered Ultrahyperfunctions
entry.summary: Withdrawn by author - Superseded by arXiv:0910.5106 [math.FA].

entry.title: Extension of CR maps of positive codimension
entry.summary: We study the holomorphic extendability of smooth CR maps between real analytic strictly pseudoconvex hypersurfaces in complex affine spaces of different dimensions.

entry.title: Riemann-Stieltjes Integral Operators between Weighted Bergman Spaces
entry.summary: This note completely describes the bounded or compact Riemann-Stieltjes integral operators $T_g$ acting between the weighted Bergman space pairs $(A^p_\alpha,A^q_\beta)$ in terms of particular regularities of the holomorphic symbols $g$ on the open unit ball of $\Bbb C^n$.

entry.title: Weighted polynomials and weighted pluripotential theory
entry.summary: We study the relation between weighted pluripotential on a compact set E in C^N and the pluripotential theory of an associated circed set Z in C^(N+1)

entry.title: Bounded Earthquakes
entry.summary: We give a short proof of the fact that bounded earthquakes of the unit disk induce quasisymmetric maps of the unit circle. By a similar method, we show that symmetric maps are induced by bounded earthquakes with asymptotically trivial measures.

entry.title: Classification of Levi degenerate homogeneous CR-manifolds in dimension 5
entry.summary: In this paper we present new examples of homogeneous 2-nondegenerate CR-manifolds of dimension 5 and give, up to local CR-equivalence, a full classification of all CR-manifolds of this type.

entry.title: Lipschitz type characterizations for Bergman Spaces
entry.summary: We obtain new characterizations for Bergman spaces with standard weights in terms of Lipschitz type conditions in the Euclidean, hyperbolic, and pseudo-hyperbolic metrics. As a consequence, we prove optimal embedding theorems when an analytic function on the unit disk is symmetrically lifted to the bidisk.

entry.title: Carleson measures for weighted Hardy-Sobolev spaces
entry.summary: We obtain characterizations of positive Borel measures $\mu$ on $\B^n$ so that some weighted Hardy-Sobolev are imbedded in $L^p(d\mu)$, where $w$ is an $A_p$ weight in the unit sphere of $\C^n$.

entry.title: On Klein-Maskit Combination Theorem in space I
entry.summary: In this paper, we generalise the first Klein-Maskit combination theorem to discrete groups of M\"{o}bius transformations in higher dimensions. As a simple application of the main theorem, some examples will be constructed.

entry.title: Overinterpolation
entry.summary: In this paper we study the consequences of overinterpolation, i.e., the situation when a function can be interpolated by polynomial, or rational, or algebraic functions in more points that normally expected. We show that in many cases such a function has specific forms.

entry.title: Hyperbolic manifolds whose envelopes of holomorphy are not hyperbolic
entry.summary: We present a family of examples of two dimensional, hyperbolic complex manifolds whose envelopes of holomorphy are not hyperbolic.

entry.title: New characterizations of Bergman spaces
entry.summary: We obtain several new characterizations for the standard weighted Bergman spaces $A^p_\alpha$ on the unit ball of $\cn$ in terms of the radial derivative, the holomorphic gradient, and the invariant gradient.
entry.arxiv:comment: Manuscript has been available online since the end of 2005

entry.title: Sur le lemme de Brody
entry.summary: Brody's lemma is a basic tool in complex hyperbolicity. We present a version of it making more precise the localization of an entire curve coming from a diverging sequence of holomorphic discs. As a byproduct we characterize hyperbolicity in terms of an isoperimetric inequality.

entry.title: Siciak-Zahariuta extremal functions and polynomial hulls
entry.summary: We use our disc formula for the Siciak-Zahariuta extremal function to characterize the polynomial hull of a connected compact subset of complex affine space in terms of analytic discs.

entry.title: Singular Levi-flat hypersurfaces and codimension one foliations
entry.summary: We study Levi-flat real analytic hypersurfaces with singularities. We prove that the Levi foliation on the regular part of the hypersurface can be holomorphically extended, in a suitable sense, to neighbourhoods of singular points.

entry.title: Sets of Approximation and Interpolation in $\cx$ for manifold-valued maps
entry.summary: We study the approximation of maps into complex manifolds along with interpolation on certain compact subsets of the plane. Results are also obtained regarding approximation and interpolation of sections of holomorphic submersions.

entry.title: Ambient metric construction of CR invariant differential operators
entry.summary: These notes are based on my lectures at IMA summer program "Symmetries and Overdetermined Systems of Partial Differential Equations." Here I try to explain basic ideas of the ambient metric construction by studying the Szego kernel of the sphere.

entry.title: Zero sets of entire functions of exponential type with some conditions on real axis
Zeroes of holomorphic functions with almost--periodic modulus
entry.summary: We give necessary and sufficient conditions for a divisor in a tube domain to be the divisor of a holomorphic function with almost--periodic modulus.

entry.title: Almost periodicity in complex analysis
entry.summary: This is a brief survey of up-to-date results on holomorphic almost periodic functions and mappings in one and several complex variables, mainly due to the Kharkov mathematical school.

entry.title: Solutions of algebraic equations with analytic almost periodic coefficients
entry.summary: A continuous solution of an algebraic equation with holomorphic almost periodic coefficients is also almost periodic.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Mat. Fizika, Analiz i Geometria, v.7, No.4 (2000), p.380-386

entry.title: Embedding Some Riemann Surfaces into \C^2 with Interpolation
entry.summary: We formalize a technique for embedding Riemann sufraces properly into \C^2, and we generalize all known embedding results to allow interpolation on prescribed discrete sequences.

entry.title: On H.Weyl and H.Minkowski Polynomials
entry.summary: We introduce certain polynomials, so-called H.Weyl and H.Minkowski polynomials, which have a geometric origin. The location of roots of these polynomials is studied.

entry.title: The Bremermann-Dirichlet problem for unbounded domains of $C^n$
entry.summary: Given an unbounded strongly pseudoconvex domain D and a continuous real valued function h defined on bD, we study the existence of a (maximal) plurisubharmonic function u on D such that u=h on bD.

entry.title: A Fatou-Bieberbach domain in C^2 which is not Runge
entry.summary: We give an example of a Fatou-Bieberbach domain which is not Runge in C^2.

entry.title: A generalization of the Levi problem with singularities
entry.summary: In this article, we prove that if $X$ is a Stein space and $\Omega\subset X$ an increasing sequence of $q$-complete open subsets, then $\Omega$ is $q$-complete.

entry.title: A Carleson type condition for interpolating sequences in the unit ball of C^n
entry.summary: In this work, we prove that if S is a dual bounded sequence in the unit ball B of C^n for the Hardy class H^p(B), then S is H^s(B) interpolating with the linear extension property.

entry.title: Corona Theorem for $H^{\infty}$ on Coverings of Riemann Surfaces of Finite Type
entry.summary: In this paper continuing our work started in our earlier papers we prove the corona theorem for the algebra of bounded holomorphic functions defined on an unbranched covering of a Caratheodory hyperbolic Riemann surface of finite type.

entry.title: Carleson measures for weighted holomorphic Besov spaces in $\C^n$
entry.summary: We obtain characterizations of positive Borel measures $\mu$ on $\B^n$ so that some weighted holomorphic Besov spaces $B_s^p(w)$ are imbedded in $L^p(d\mu)$, where $w$ is a $B_p$ weight in the unit ball of $\C^n$.

entry.title: Complex Analysis as Catalyst
entry.summary: We illustrate the general principle that complex analysis can be a good setting for posing problems that are best solved using techniques from other mathematical disciplines. Several examples are provided.

entry.title: Hardy and Bergman spaces on hyperconvex domains and their composition operators
entry.summary: In thius paper we introduce the Hardy and Bergman spaces on hyperconvex domains relative to a acontinuous exhaustion function. We prove their basic properties and study their composition operators induced by holomorphic mappings between domains.

entry.title: Interpolating and sampling sequences in finite Riemann surfaces
entry.summary: We provide a description of the interpolating and sampling sequences on a space of holomorphic functions with a uniform growth restriction defined on finite Riemann surfaces.

entry.title: Proper holomorphic mappings of the spectral unit ball
entry.summary: We prove an Alexander type theorem for the spectral unit ball $\Omega_n$ showing that there are no non-trivial proper holomorphic mappings in $\Omega_n$, $n\geq 2$.

entry.title: Extension theorems of Sakai type for separately holomorphic and meromorphic functions
entry.summary: We first exhibit counterexamples to some open questions related to a theorem of Sakai. Then we establish an extension theorem of Sakai type for separately holomorphic/meromorphic functions.

entry.title: Pseudocontinuation and cyclicity for random power series
entry.summary: We prove that a random function in the Hardy space $H^2$ is a non-cyclic vector for the backward shift operator almost surely. The question of existence of a local pseudocontinuation for a random analytic function is also studied.

entry.title: Natural boundary of Dirichlet series
entry.summary: We prove some conditions on the existence of natural boundaries of Dirichlet series. We show that generically the presumed boundary is the natural one. We also give an application of natural boundaries in determining asymptotic results.

entry.title: An Inequality for Mixed Monge-Amp√®re measures
entry.summary: We generalize an inequality for mixed Monge-Amp\`ere measures. We also give an example that shows that our assumptions are sharp. The corresponding result in the setting of compact K\"ahler manifold is also discussed.

entry.title: Modular equations of order $p$ and Theta functions
entry.summary: An algorithm to obtain equations between theta functions with integral characteristics evaluated at $\tau$ and $p\tau$ for $g>1$ is presented.
entry.arxiv:comment: 7 pages expanded proofs fixed references and grammar errors to appear in albanian journal of mathematics

entry.title: On the dynamics of codimension one holomorphic foliations with ample normal bundle
entry.summary: We investigate the accumulation to singular points of leaves of codimension one foliations whose normal bundle is ample, with emphasis on the nonexistence of Levi-flat hypersurfaces.

entry.title: The characterization of the Carleson measures for analytic Besov spaces: a simple proof
entry.summary: We give a simple proof of the characterization of the Carleson measures for the weighted analytic Besov spaces. Such characterization provides some information on the radial variation of an analytic Besov function.

entry.title: Proper holomorphic disks in the complement of varieties in \C^2
entry.summary: For any closed analytic set X in C^2 there exists a proper holomorphic embedding of the unit disk into C^2 such that the image avoids X.

entry.title: The Edge of the Wedge Theorem for Tempered Ultrahyperfunctions II. A Generalized Version
entry.summary: Withdrawn by author - Superseded by arXiv:0910.5106 [math.FA].

entry.title: On the scaling limit of a singular integral operator
entry.summary: The scaling limit and Schauder bounds are derived for a singular integral operator arising from a difference equation approach to monodromy problems.

entry.title: Sur les fonctions √† singularit√© de dimension 1
entry.summary: In this article we show that all results proved for a large class of holomorphic germs $f : (\mathbb{C}^{n+1}, 0) \to (\mathbb{C}, 0)$ with a 1-dimension singularity in [B.II] are valid for an arbitrary such germ.

entry.title: On the Wu metric in unbounded domains
entry.summary: We discuss the properties of the Wu pseudometric and present counterexamples for its upper semicontinuity that answers the question posed by Jarnicki and Pflug. We also give formulae for the Wu pseudometric in elementary Reinhardt domains.

entry.title: Analytic continuation of residue currents
entry.summary: Let $X$ be a complex manifold and $f\colon X\to \C^p$ a holomorphic mapping defining a complete intersection. We prove that the iterated Mellin transform of the residue integral associated to $f$ has an analytic continuation to a neighborhood of the origin in $\C^p$.

entry.title: On an inequality concerning the polar derivative of a polynomial
entry.summary: In this paper, we present a correct proof of an $L_p$-inequality concerning the polar derivative of a polynomial with restricted zeros. We also extend Zygmund's inequality to the polar derivative of a polynomial.

entry.title: Ullemar's formula for the moment map, II
entry.summary: We establish the complex analogue of Ullemar's formula for polynomial domains. We show that the Jacobian of the complex moment mapping is equal to the self-resultant of the defining polynomial.

entry.title: On harmonic quasiconformal quasi-isometries
entry.summary: The purpose of this paper is to explore conditions which guarantee Lipschitz-continuity of harmonic maps w.r.t. quasihyperbolic metrics. For instance, we prove that harmonic quasiconformal maps are Lipschitz w.r.t. quasihyperbolic metrics.

entry.title: Peak points for pseudoconvex domains: a survey
entry.summary: This paper surveys results concerning peak points for pseudoconvex domains. It includes results of Laszlo that have not been published elsewhere.
entry.arxiv:comment: 40 pages; polished a bit, and a few more references added; accepted for publication in J. Geom. Anal

entry.title: Filling real hypersurfaces by pseudoholomorphic discs
entry.summary: We study pseudoholomorphic discs with boundaries attached to a real hypersurface in an almost complex manifold. We give sufficient conditions for filling a one sided neighborhood of the hypersurface by the discs.

entry.title: An Analytic Proof of the Matrix Spectral Factorization Theorem
entry.summary: An analytic proof is proposed of Wiener's theorem on factorization of positive definite matrix-functions.

entry.title: Integral means spectrum of random conformal snowflakes
entry.summary: In this paper we construct random conformal snowflakes with large integral means spectrum at different points. These new estimates are significant improvement over previously known lower bound of the universal spectrum. Our estimates are within 5-10 percent from the conjectured value of the universal spectrum.

entry.title: Remarks on weakly pseudoconvex boundaries: Erratum
entry.summary: We make two tiny corrections to our previous paper with the same title, and also obtain, as a bonus, something new.

entry.title: Stein or Milnor fillability and cohomology
entry.summary: I have withdrawn the paper, after having incorporated it into the paper arXiv:0712.3484. In the meantime I have discovered that one of the theorems proved in the paper had already been proved by Durfee & Hain.

entry.title: On the estimation of the convergence rate in the Janashia-Lagvilava spectral factorization algorithm
entry.summary: In the present paper, we estimate the convergence rate in the Janashia-Lagvilava spectral factorization algorithm (see Studia Mathematica, 137, 1999, 93-100) under the restriction on a spectral density matrix that its inverse is integrable.

entry.title: Holomorphic fillability and cohomology
entry.summary: I have withdrawn the paper, after having incorporated it into the paper arXiv:0712.3484. In the meantime I have discovered that the main theorem proved in the paper had already been proved by Bungart.

entry.title: Finite unions of balls in C^n are rationally convex
entry.summary: It is shown that the rational convexity of any finite union of disjoint closed balls in C^n follows easily from the results of Duval and Sibony.

entry.title: Holomorphic L^{p}-functions on Coverings of Strongly Pseudoconvex Manifolds
entry.summary: In this paper we will show how to construct holomorphic L^{p}-functions on unbranched coverings of strongly pseudoconvex manifolds. Also, we prove some extension and approximation theorems for such functions.

entry.title: Analytic continuation from a family of lines
entry.summary: Given a function f in the exterior of a convex curve in the real plane, we prove that if the restrictions of f to the tangent lines to the curve extend as entire functions, then the function f is an entire function of two variables.

entry.title: Theory of Bergman spaces (I)
entry.summary: These notes are part of the research seminar with title "Theory of Bergman spaces and related function spaces" that took place in the University of Crete, Department of Mathematics (September 2006- December 2007), in the framework of the research program PYTHAGORAS II(75% European funds--25% Greek national funds).

entry.title: Remarks on Lempert functions of balanced domains
entry.summary: This note should clarify how the behavior of certain invariant objects reflects the geometric convexity of balanced domains.
entry.arxiv:comment: to appear in the Monatsh. Math.

entry.title: Analyticity and propagation of plurisubharmonic singularities
entry.summary: A variant of Siu's analyticity theorem is proved for relative types of plurisubharmonic functions. Some results on propagation of plurisubharmonic singularities and maximality of pluricomplex Green functions with analytic singularities are derived.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Functional Analysis and Complex Analysis. Contemporary Mathematics, Vol. 481, 137-143. AMS, 2009.

entry.title: Lipschitzness of the Lempert and Green functions
entry.summary: Necessary and sufficient conditions for Lipschitzness of the Lempert and Green functions are found in terms of their boundary behaviors.

entry.title: Closed ideals in some algebras of analytic functions
entry.summary: We obtain a complete description of closed ideals of the algebra $\mathcal{D}\cap \mathrm{lip}_\alpha},$ $0<\alpha\leq{1/2},$ where $\mathcal{D}$ is the Dirichlet space and $\mathrm{lip}_\alpha}$ is the algebra of analytic functions satisfying the Lipschitz condition of order $\alpha.$

entry.title: On approximation of continuous functions by entire functions on subsets of the real line
entry.summary: We generalize the classical Bernstein theorem concerning the constructive description of classes of functions uniformly continuous on the real line. The approximation of continuous bounded functions by entire functions of exponential type on unbounded closed proper subsets of the real line is studded.

entry.title: Formal meromorphic functions on manifolds of finite type
entry.summary: It is shown that a real-valued formal meromorphic function on a formal generic submanifold of finite Kohn-Bloom-Graham type is necessarily constant.

entry.title: A Kobayashi metric version of Bun Wong's theorem
entry.summary: We prove that a strongly pseudoconvex domain with noncompact group of Kobayashi/Royden metric isometries must be biholomorphic to the unit ball.

entry.title: Note on constancy of some formal meromorphic maps
entry.summary: Segre sets are superfluous to verify that quotients of formal holomorphic maps that are real on a minimal generic submanifold of positive CR dimension must necessarily be constant.

entry.title: On a question of Koll√°r
entry.summary: We show: If a bounded domain in a Stein space covers a compact complex space, it must be smooth. This give a negative answer to a question of Koll\'ar. Furthermore, we deduce some related results.

entry.title: Uniqueness and Stability in $\mathcal E(X,œâ)$
entry.summary: We prove uniqueness for the Dirichlet problem for the complex Monge-Amp\`ere equation on compact K\"ahler manifolds in the case of measures vanishing on pluripolar sets. As a by-product we generalize Xing's stability theorem.

entry.title: Hypergeometric functions and hyperbolic metric
entry.summary: We obtain new inequalities for certain hypergeometric functions. Using these inequalities, we deduce estimates for the hyperbolic metric and the induced distance function on a certain canonical hyperbolic plane domain.

entry.title: On a Monge-Amp√®re type equation in the Cegrell class $\mathcal{E}_œá$
entry.summary: In this paper we prove an existence and uniqueness result for a Monge-Amp\`{e}re type equation in the Cegrell class $\mathcal{E}_{\chi}$.

entry.title: Proper holomorphic mapppings between Reinhardt domains in $\mathbb C^2$
entry.summary: We describe all possibilities of existence of non-elementary proper holomorphic maps between non-hyperbolic Reinhardt domains in $\mathbb C^2$ and the corresponding pairs of domains.

entry.title: Infinite-dimensionality of the Automorphism Groups of Homogeneous Stein Manifolds
entry.summary: We show that the group of holomorphic automorphisms of a Stein manifold X of dimension greater than 1 is infinite-dimensional, provided X is a homogeneous space of a holomorphic action of a complex Lie group.

entry.title: Rational convexity of non generic immersed lagrangian submanifolds
entry.summary: We prove that an immersed lagrangian submanifold in $\C^n$ with quadratic self-tangencies is rationally convex. This generalizes former results for the embedded and the immersed transversal cases.

entry.title: Semiweak Cullen-regular quaternionic functions
entry.summary: We introduce the class of semiweak Cullen-regular quaternionic functions by interpreting Cullen-regular functions as solutions to an inhomogeneous PDE in terms of the Fueter operator.

entry.title: Sur la Caracterisation des Retractes Holomorphes a l'aide de la Metrique Infinitesimale de Kobayashi
entry.summary: Dans cet article, on donne une caracterisation des retractes holomorphes a l'aide de la metrique infinitesimale de Kobayashi ----- This article gives a characterization of holomorphic retractions using Kobayashi's infinitesimal metric.

entry.title: An extremal problem for a class of entire functions of exponential type
entry.summary: We find the exact upper estimate for the upper density of zeros of entire functions of exponential type whose indicator diagram is contained in a given interval.

entry.title: Note on the growth of Area functions
entry.summary: A new proof of the inequalities of D. J. Hallenbeck for the Area functions of multipliers of fractional Cauchy transforms is given.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Journal of Technical University at Plovdiv: Fundamental Sciences and Applications, Vol. 6, 1998 pgs 37-40

entry.title: On quasiconformal maps with identity boundary values
entry.summary: Quasiconformal homeomorphisms of the unit ball $B^n$ of ${\mathbb R}^n, n \ge 3,$ onto itself with identity boundary values are studied. A spatial analogue of Teichm\"uller's theorem is proved.

entry.title: BMOA estimates and radial growth of $B_œÜ$ functions
entry.summary: BMO estimates and the radial growth of Bloch functions have been studied by B. Korenblum [3]. The present paper contains some natural generalizations of these results.

entry.title: A Tale of Three Kernels
