entry.summary: We consider the Bergman, Szeg\H{o}, and Poisson Szeg\H{o} kernels on a domain in $\CC$ or $\CC^n$. Various properties and relationships are established. The paper has both an expository component and a research component.

entry.title: Inequalities for analytic functions with the derivative in H1
entry.summary: It is proved an inequality - integrated analogue of the Hardy inequality and as application simplified proof of the theorem of S. A. Vinogradov for the bounded Toeplitz operators on the space of functions analytic and bounded in the unit disc is given.

entry.title: The Kobayashi metric in the normal direction and the mapping problem
entry.summary: Estimates of the Kobayashi metric in the normal direction are used to study the mapping problem in several complex variables.
entry.arxiv:comment: 13 pages; to appear in the special issue of Complex Variables and Elliptic Equations on holomorphic mappings edited by Steven Krantz and John Erik Fornaess

entry.title: Geometric properties and related results for holomorphic Segre preserving maps
entry.summary: In this paper, we examine holomorphic Segre preserving maps between the complexifications of real hypersurfaces in $\mathbb{C}^{n+1}$. In particular, we find several sufficient conditions ensuring that Segre transversality and total Segre nondegeneracy of the maps must hold.

entry.title: On injectivity of quasiregular mappings
entry.summary: We give sufficient conditions for a planar quasiregular mapping to be injective in terms of the range of the differential matrix.

entry.title: A Rigidity Condition for Holomorphic Generator in Strongly Convex Domains
entry.summary: In this paper I give a condition, in terms of boundary behaviour, that forces the infinitesimal generator of a one-parameter semigroup of holomorphic maps to vanish.

entry.title: A non-existence theorem for Morse type holomorphic foliations of codimension one transverse to spheres
entry.summary: We prove that a Morse type codimension one holomorphic foliation is not transverse to a sphere in the complex affine space. Also we characterize the variety of contacts of a linear foliation with concentric spheres.

entry.title: Regularizations of residue currents
entry.summary: Under assumptions about complete intersection, we prove that Coleff-Herrera type currents satisfy a robust calculus in the sense that natural regularizations of such currents can be multiplied to yield regularizations of the Coleff-Herrera product of the currents.

entry.title: Holomorphic factorization of mappings into SL_n(C)
entry.summary: We solve Gromov's Vaserstein problem. Namely, we show that a null-homotopic holomorphic mapping from a finite dimensional reduced Stein space into SL_n(C) can be factored into a finite product of unipotent matrices with holomorphic entries.

entry.title: Estimates for invariant metrics on $\Bbb C$-convex domains
entry.summary: Geometric lower and upper estimates are obtained for invariant metrics on $\Bbb C$-convex domains containing no complex lines.

entry.title: Normal forms and linearization of holomorphic dilation type semigroups in several variables
entry.summary: In this paper we study commuting families of holomorphic mappings in $\mathbb{C}^n$ which form abelian semigroups with respect to their real parameter. Linearization models for holomorphic mappings are been used in the spirit of Schr\"oder's classical functional equation.

entry.title: Intrinsic Differential Geometry and the Existence of Quasimeromorphic Mappings
entry.summary: We give a new proof of the existence of nontrivial quasimeromorphic mappings on a smooth Riemannian manifold, using solely the intrinsic geometry of the manifold.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Revue Roumaine de Math. Pures et Appl., 54 (2009), 5-6, 565-574

entry.title: Recent developments in the theory of separately holomorphic mappings
entry.summary: We describe a part of the recent developments in the theory of separately holomorphic mappings between complex analytic spaces. Our description focuses on works using the technique of holomorphic discs.
entry.arxiv:comment: 29 pages; A previous version is available at the ICTP preprint website (ref. IC2007074)

entry.title: The size of Wiman-Valiron disks
entry.summary: Wiman-Valiron theory and results of Macintyre about "flat regions" describe the asymptotic behavior of entire functions in certain disks around points of maximum modulus. We estimate the size of these disks for Macintyre's theory from above and below.

entry.title: Affine and wrap algebras over octonions
entry.summary: The article is devoted to affine and wrap algebras over quaternions and octonions. Residues of functions of quaternion and octonion variables are studied. They are used for construction of such algebras. Their structure is investigated.

entry.title: Boundary Values and Boundary Uniqueness of $J$-Holomorphic Mapping
entry.summary: We establish a Fatou-type Theorem for $J$-holomorphic mappings that are bounded in an appropriate sense and we prove the Blaschke condition for their zero sets. We also prove a Privalov-type uniqueness Theorem for pairs of $J$-holomorphic mappings.

entry.title: Subclasses of Meromorphic Starlike Functions
entry.summary: The object of this paper is studying some properties of meromorphic functions which satisfy in the condition \[Re(zf(z)) > \alpha|z^2f'(z)+zf(z)| .\] Parallel results for some related classes are also obtained.

entry.title: Typically Real Harmonic Functions
entry.summary: We consider a class $\THO$ of typically real harmonic functions on the unit disk that contains the class of normalized analytic and typically real functions. We also obtain some partial results about the region of univalence for this class.

entry.title: Non-real zeros of derivatives of real meromorphic functions
entry.summary: The main result of the paper determines all real meromorphic functions of finite order in the plane for which the first derivative has finitely many zeros, while the function itself and one of its higher derivatives have finitely many non-real zeros.

entry.title: On calculus with a quaternionic variable and its characteristic Cauchy-Riemann type equations
entry.summary: We show sufficient and necessary conditions, in terms of some partial differential equations with variable coefficients, for a quaternionic function to admit a continuous derivative in a open set in the sense of C. Schwartz.

entry.title: Continuation of CR-Automorphisms of Levi Degenerate Hyperquadrics to the Projective Space
entry.summary: We show that every CR-automorphism of the closure of a Levi degenerate hyperquadric in the projective space extends to a holomorphic automorphism of the projective space.

entry.title: Integral representations on non-smooth domains
entry.summary: We derive integral representations for $(0,q)$-forms, $q\ge1$, on non-smooth strictly pseudoconvex domains, the Henkin-Leiterer domains. A $(0,q)$-form, $f$ is written in terms of integral operators acting on $f$, $\mdbar f$, and $\mdbar^{\ast} f$. The representation is applied to derive $L^{\infty}$ estimates.

entry.title: Courants du type residuel attach√©s √† une intersection compl√®te
entry.summary: We construct in complete intersection's case, elementary currents which describe the local ideal, and give a decomposition in it for holomorphic function.

entry.title: Dimension of quasicircles
entry.summary: We introduce canonical antisymmetric quasiconformal maps, which minimize the quasiconformality constant among maps sending the unit circle to a given quasicircle. As an application we prove Astala's conjecture that the Hausdorff dimension of a $k$-quasicircle is at most $1+k^2$.

entry.title: Distribution of Normalized Zero-Sets of Random Entire Functions with Small Random Perturbation
entry.summary: In this paper, we extend our earlier result (see [Y-2008]) on the distribution of normalized zero-sets of random entire functions to random entire functions with small random perturbation.

entry.title: H√∂lder continuous potentials on manifolds with partially positive curvature
entry.summary: It is proved that solutions of the complex Monge-Amp\`ere equation on compact K\"ahler manifolds with right hand side in $L^p, p>1$ are uniformly H\"older continuous under the assumption on non-negative orthogonal bisectional curvature.

entry.title: Certain Subclasses of Convex functions with positive and missing Coefficients by using a fixed point
entry.summary: By considering a fixed point in unit disk $\Delta$, a new class of univalent convex functions is defined. Coefficient inequalities, integral operator and extreme points of this class are obtained.

entry.title: Serre problem for unbounded pseudoconvex Reinhardt domains in $\mathbb C^2$
entry.summary: A characterization of non-hyperbolic pseudoconvex Reinhardt domains in $\mathbb C^2$ for which the answer to the Serre problem is positive is given.

entry.title: Convergence in capacity on compact K√§hler manifolds
entry.summary: The aim of this note is to study the convergence in capacity for functions in the class $\mathcal E(X,\omega)$. We obtain several stability theorems. Some of these are (optimal) generalizations of results of Xing, while others are new.

entry.title: Operator Bezoutiant and Roots of Entire Functions, Concrete Examples
entry.summary: In this paper we use the Bezoutiant method to describe the conditions under which two entire functions have not common roots. We apply the general results to concrete examples. In particular we consider the Bessel functions.

entry.title: Riemann Zeta Function
entry.summary: Global mapping properties of the Riemann Zeta function are used to investigate its non trivial zeros.

entry.title: Convexity of Hessian Integrals and Poincare Type Inequalities
entry.summary: In this paper, we studied integrals involving both real and complex Hessian operators over bounded domain. Poincare type inequalities were proved in both cases which generalized a early results of Trudinger and Wang.

entry.title: Approximation of analytic sets with proper projection by algebraic sets
entry.summary: Let $X$ be an analytic subset of $U\times C^n$ of pure dimension $k$ such that the projection of $X$ onto $U$ is a proper mapping, where $U$ is a Runge domain in $C^k$. We show that $X$ can be approximated by algebraic sets.

entry.title: Invariant CR Mappings
entry.summary: We summarize some work on CR mappings invariant under a subgroup of U(n) and prove a result on the failure of rigidity.
entry.arxiv:comment: to appear in Complex Analysis: Several complex variables and connections with PDEs and geometry (Fribourg 2008), Trends in Math, Birkh\"auser-Verlag

entry.title: Subelliptic Estimates
entry.summary: We discuss some aspects of the theory of subelliptic estimates.
entry.arxiv:comment: to appear in Complex Analysis: Several complex variables and connections with PDEs and geometry (Fribourg 2008), Trends in Math, Birkh\"auser-Verlag

entry.title: Dual mean value problem for complex polynomials
entry.summary: We consider an extremal problem for polynomials, which is dual to the well-known Smale mean value problem. We give a rough estimate depending only on the degree.

entry.title: Characterization of domains in $\mathbb C^n$ by their noncompact automorphism groups
entry.summary: In this paper, the characterization of domains in $\mathbb C^n$ by their noncompact automorphism groups are given.

entry.title: Cross theorem with singularities - pluripolar vs. analytic case
entry.summary: We prove that in the extension theorem for separately holomorphic functions on an $N$-fold cross with singularities the case of analytic singularities follows from the case of pluripolar singularities.

entry.title: Fatou-Bieberbach domains as basins of attraction of automorphisms tangent to the identity
entry.summary: We prove that there exists an automorphism of C^2 tangent to the identity with a domain of attraction to the origin, biholomorphic to the origin, along a degenerate characteristic direction.

entry.title: CR-quadrics with a symmetry property
entry.summary: Motivated by the Shilov boundaries of bounded symmetric domains we consider arbitrary CR-quadrics in a complex linear space (of finite dimension) that have a certain symmetry property. For these the non-affine local CR-automorphisms have a simple explicit description. A large class of examples is presented.

entry.title: Normed domains of holomorphy
entry.summary: We treat the classical concept of domain of holomorphy in $\CC^n$ when the holomorphic functions considered are restricted to lie in some Banach space. Positive and negative results are presented. A new view of the case $n = 1$ is considered.

entry.title: Divisorial Zariski decomposition and algebraic Morse inequalities
entry.summary: In this note we use the divisorial Zariski decomposition to give a more intrinsic version of the algebraic Morse inequalities.
entry.arxiv:comment: In this version we correct some misprints.

entry.title: Frame Constants of Gabor Frames near the Critical Density
entry.summary: We consider Gabor frames generated by a Gaussian function and describe the behavior of the frame constants as the density of the lattice approaches the critical value.

entry.title: A New Method of Matrix Spectral Factorization
entry.summary: A new method of matrix spectral factorization is proposed which reliably computes an approximate spectral factor of any matrix spectral density that admits spectral factorization

entry.title: Boundary behavior of the Kobayashi-Royden metric in smooth pseudoconvex domains
entry.summary: We show some lower estimates for the Kobayashi-Royden metric on a class of smooth bounded pseudoconvex domains.
entry.arxiv:comment: 9 pages, some minor corrections are made

entry.title: Homogeneous CR-solvmanifolds as Kahler obstructions
entry.summary: We give a precise characterization when a compact homogeneous CR-solvmanifold is CR-embeddable in a Kahler manifold. Equivalently this gives a non-Kahler criterion for complex manifolds containing CR-solvmanifolds not satisfying these conditions. This paper is the natural continuation of [OR] and [GOR].

entry.title: Riemann surfaces and totally real tori
entry.summary: Given a generic totally real torus unknotted in the unit sphere of the complex plane, we prove the following alternative : either there exists a filling of the torus by holomorphic discs and the torus is rationally convex, or its rational hull contains a holomorphic annulus.

entry.title: On some $n$-starlike integral operators
entry.summary: By a completion of a lemma of Babalola and Opoola \cite{KT}, we prove that certain generalized integral operators preserve $n$-starlikeness in the open unit disk $E=\{z\in \mathbb{C}: |z|<1\}$. Our results generalize, extend and improve many known ones.

entry.title: Integral means of analytic mappings by iteration of Janowski functions
entry.summary: In this short note we apply certain iteration of the Janowski functions to estimate the integral means of some analytic and univalent mappings of $|z|<1$. Our method of proof follows an earlier one due to Leung \cite{YJ}.
